body:
Context: /moretypes/14

When entering `i^j` as a literal, cool stuff happens.

When using math.Pow to calculate and enter it, much less cool stuff happens, IMHO.

Why is math.Pow suggested?

```
package main

import "golang.org/x/tour/pic"

func Pic(dx, dy int) [][]uint8 {
	sos := make([][]uint8, dy)
	for i := 0; i < dy; i++ {
		sos[i] = make([]uint8, dx)
		for j := 0; j < dx; j++ {
//		  sos[i][j] = uint8(i*j)
		  sos[i][j] = uint8(i^j)
		}
	}
	
	return sos
}

func main() {
	pic.Show(Pic)
}
```
